{{italic title}} {{Taxobox | color = lightgrey | name = Acidicapsa borealis | image = | image_caption = | regnum = [[Bacteria]] | phylum = [[Acidobacteria]] | classis = [[Acidobacteria]] | ordo = [[Acidobacteriales]] | familia = [[Acidobacteriaceae]] | genus = ''[[Acidicapsa]]'' | species = '''''A. borealis''''' | binomial = ''Acidicapsa borealis'' | binomial_authority = Kulichevskaya et al. 2012<ref name="Acidicapsa-borealis">{{cite journal|last1=Parte|first1=A.C.|title=Acidicapsa|journal=www.bacterio.net|url=http://www.bacterio.net/acidicapsa.html}}</ref> | type_strain = DSM 23886, KA1, LMG 25897, VKM B-2678<ref>{{cite journal|title=Acidicapsa borealis Taxon Passport - StrainInfo|journal=www.straininfo.net|url=http://www.straininfo.net/taxa/380810;jsessionid=09C525A27FB279DF6D1F724DC9759D81.straininfo2}}</ref> | subdivision = | synonyms = }}
'''''Acidicapsa borealis''''' is a [[Gram-negative]], short rods and non-motile bacterium from the genus of [[Acidicapsa]] which has been isolated from [[sphagnum]] peat from the [[Tver Region]] in [[Russia]].<ref name="Acidicapsa-borealis"/><ref>{{cite journal|title=Acidicapsa borealis|journal=www.uniprot.org|url=https://www.uniprot.org/taxonomy/946336}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Details: DSM-23886|journal=www.dsmz.de|url=https://www.dsmz.de/catalogues/details/culture/DSM-23886.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Kulichevskaya|first1=I. S.|last2=Kostina|first2=L. A.|last3=Valaskova|first3=V.|last4=Rijpstra|first4=W. I. C.|last5=Sinninghe Damste|first5=J. S.|last6=de Boer|first6=W.|last7=Dedysh|first7=S. N.|title=Acidicapsa borealis gen. nov., sp. nov. and Acidicapsa ligni sp. nov., subdivision 1 Acidobacteria from Sphagnum peat and decaying wood|journal=International Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Microbiology|date=19 August 2011|volume=62|issue=Pt 7|pages=1512–1520|doi=10.1099/ijs.0.034819-0|pmid=21856984}}</ref>
