{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Altimir Glacier | other_name = | photo = Ant-pen map anvers.PNG | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Location of Anvers Island in the Antarctic Peninsula region | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Altimir Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = | location = [[Anvers Island]] | coordinates = {{coord|64|35|50|S|63|09|00|W|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = {{convert|4.8|km|mi|abbr=on}} | width = {{convert|5.5|km|mi|abbr=on}} | thickness = | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Fournier Bay]] | status = | embedded = }}
'''Altimir Glacier''' ({{lang-bg|italic=yes|ледник Алтимир}}, 'Lednik Altimir' \'led-nik al-ti-'mir\) is a {{convert|4.8|km|adj=on}} long and {{convert|5.5|km|adj=on}} wide glacier draining the north slopes of the [[Osterrieth Range]] on [[Anvers Island]] in the [[Palmer Archipelago]], [[Antarctica]]. It flows northwards to enter [[Dalchev Cove]] in [[Fournier Bay]] east of [[Studena Point]].
The glacier is named after the settlement of [[Altimir]] in northwestern [[Bulgaria]].
==Location== Altimir Glacier is located at {{coord|64|35|50|S|63|09|00|W|display=inline,title}}. It was mapped by the British [[Directorate of Overseas Surveys]] in 1980.
==See also== * [[List of glaciers in the Antarctic]] * [[Glaciology]]
