{{Expand Estonian|date=December 2008|Eerik Kumari}} [[File:Kumari kivi.JPG|thumb|right|Eerik Kumari memorial stone in [[Puhtu]] biological station.]] '''Eerik Kumari''' (7 March 1912 in [[Kirbla]], [[Lihula Parish]] – 8 January 1984; born as '''Erik Mathias Sits''') was a doctor of [[biology]], the founder of [[ornithology]] and nature [[Habitat conservation|conservation]] in [[Estonia]], the learned director of the Institute of Zoology and Botany at the [[Estonian Academy of Sciences]] during 1952-1977. He was the president of the [[Estonian Naturalists' Society]] in 1954–1964.
The [[Eerik Kumari Award]] was established in 1989 in his name to honor those who have excelled in bioscience in Estonia.
