This page lists published welding codes, procedures, and specifications.
== American Society of Mechanical Engineers (ASME) Codes == The [[American Society of Mechanical Engineers]] (ASME) [[ASME Boiler and Pressure Vessel Code (BPVC)|Boiler and Pressure Vessel Code]] (BPVC) covers all aspects of design and manufacture of boilers and pressure vessels. All sections contain welding specifications, however most relevant information is contained in the following: {| class="wikitable sortable" ! Code !! Description |- | ASME BPVC Section I || Rules for Construction of Power Boilers |- | ASME BPVC Section II || Part C: Specifications for Welding Rods, Electrodes, and Filler Metals.{{efn|Actually the ASME code adopts the AWS 5.* series of specifications and renames them as SFA 5.*}} |- |ASME BPVC Section III |Rules for Constructions of Nuclear Facility Components-Subsection NCA-General Requirements for Division 1 and Division 2 |- |ASME BPVC Section IV |Rules for Construction of Heating Boilers |- |ASME BPVC Section V||Nondestructive Examination |- |ASME BPVC Section VIII |Rules for Construction of Pressure Vessels Division 1 and Division 2 |- |ASME BPVC Section IX||Welding and Brazing Qualifications |- |ASME B16.25||Buttwelding ends |- |ASME B31.1 ||Power Piping |- |ASME B31.3 ||Process Piping. |}
==American Welding Society (AWS) Standards== The [[American Welding Society]] (AWS) publishes over 241 AWS-developed codes, recommended practices and guides which are written in accordance with American National Standards Institute (ANSI) practices.<ref>{{cite web|title=American Welding Society - Technical|url=http://www.aws.org/technical/|publisher=American Welding Society|accessdate=7 November 2011}}</ref> The following is a partial list of the more common publications: {| class="wikitable sortable" !Standard Number !! Title |- |data-sort-value="AWS A02.4" | AWS A2.4 || Standard symbols for welding, brazing, and non-destructive examination |- |data-sort-value="AWS A03.0" | AWS A3.0 || Standard welding terms and definitions |- |data-sort-value="AWS A05.1" | AWS A5.1 || Specification for carbon steel electrodes for shielded metal arc welding |- |data-sort-value="AWS A05.18" | AWS A5.18 || Specification for carbon steel electrodes and rods for gas shielded arc welding |- |data-sort-value="AWS B1.10" | AWS B1.10 || Guide for the nondestructive examination of welds |- |data-sort-value="AWS B02.1" | AWS B2.1 || Specification for Welding Procedure and Performance Qualification |- |data-sort-value="AWS D01.1" |AWS D1.1||Structural welding (steel) |- |data-sort-value="AWS D01.2" |AWS D1.2||Structural welding (aluminum) |- |data-sort-value="AWS D01.3" |AWS D1.3||Structural welding (sheet steel) |- |data-sort-value="AWS D01.4" |AWS D1.4||Structural welding (reinforcing steel) |- |data-sort-value="AWS D01.5" |AWS D1.5||Bridge welding |- |data-sort-value="AWS D01.6" |AWS D1.6||Structural welding (stainless steel) |- |data-sort-value="AWS D01.7" |AWS D1.7||Structural welding (strengthening and repair) |- |data-sort-value="AWS D01.8" |AWS D1.8||Structural welding seismic supplement |- |data-sort-value="AWS D01.9" |AWS D1.9||Structural welding (titanium) |- |data-sort-value="AWS D3.6R" |AWS D3.6R||Underwater welding (Offshore 7 inland pipelines) |- |data-sort-value="AWS D08.1" |AWS D8.1||Automotive spot welding |- |data-sort-value="AWS D08.6" |AWS D8.6||Automotive spot welding electrodes supplement |- |data-sort-value="AWS D08.7" |AWS D8.7||Automotive spot welding recommendations supplement |- |data-sort-value="AWS D08.8" |AWS D8.8||Automotive arc welding (steel) |- |data-sort-value="AWS D08.9" |AWS D8.9||Automotive spot weld testing |- |data-sort-value="AWS D08.14" |AWS D8.14||Automotive arc welding (aluminum) |- |data-sort-value="AWS D09.1" |AWS D9.1||Sheet metal welding |- |data-sort-value="AWS D10.10" |AWS D10.10||Heating practices for pipe and tube |- |data-sort-value="AWS D10.11" |AWS D10.11||Root pass welding for pipe |- |data-sort-value="AWS D10.12" |AWS D10.12||Pipe welding (mild steel) |- |data-sort-value="AWS D10.13" |AWS D10.13||Tube brazing (copper) |- |data-sort-value="AWS D10.18" |AWS D10.18||Pipe welding (stainless steel) |- |data-sort-value="AWS D11.2" |AWS D11.2||Welding (cast iron) |- |data-sort-value="AWS D14.1" |AWS D14.1||Industrial mill crane welding |- |data-sort-value="AWS D14.3" |AWS D14.3||Earthmoving & agricultural equipment welding |- |data-sort-value="AWS D14.4" |AWS D14.4||Machinery joint welding |- |data-sort-value="AWS D14.5" |AWS D14.5||Press welding |- |data-sort-value="AWS D14.6" |AWS D14.6||Rotating Elements of Equipment |- |data-sort-value="AWS D15.1" |AWS D15.1||Railroad welding |- |data-sort-value="AWS D15.2" |AWS D15.2||Railroad welding practice supplement |- |data-sort-value="AWS D16.1" |AWS D16.1||Robotic arc welding safety |- |data-sort-value="AWS D16.2" |AWS D16.2||Robotic arc welding system installation |- |data-sort-value="AWS D16.3" |AWS D16.3||Robotic arc welding risk assessment |- |data-sort-value="AWS D16.4" |AWS D16.4||Robotic arc welder operator qualification |- |data-sort-value="AWS D17.1" |AWS D17.1||Aerospace fusion welding |- |data-sort-value="AWS D17.2" |AWS D17.2||Aerospace resistance welding |- |data-sort-value="AWS D18.1" |AWS D18.1||Hygienic tube welding (stainless steel) |- |dat