==American Petroleum Institute (API) Standards== The [[American Petroleum Institute]] (API) oldest and most successful programs is in the development of API standards which started with its first standard in 1924. API maintains over 500 standards covering the oil and gas field.<ref>{{cite web|title=American Petroleum Institute Standards|url=http://www.api.org/Standards/|publisher=American Petroleum Institute|accessdate=7 November 2011}}</ref> The following is a partial list specific to welding:
{| class="wikitable sortable" !Standard Number!!Description |- |API RP 577 || Welding Inspection and Metallurgy |- |API RP 582||Welding Guidelines for the Chemical, Oil, and Gas Industries |- |API 1104||Welding of pipelines and related facilities |}
==Australian / New Zealand (AS/NZS) Standards== [[Standards Australia]] is the body responsible for the development, maintenance and publication of Australian Standards.<ref>{{cite web|title=Standards Development|url=http://www.standards.org.au/OurRoles/StandardsDevelopment.aspx|publisher=Standards Australia|accessdate=7 November 2011}}</ref> The following is a partial list specific to welding: {| class="wikitable sortable" !Standard Number!!Description |- |AS/NZS 1554.1||Structural steel welding - Welding of steel structures |- |AS/NZS 1554.2||Structural steel welding - Stud welding (steel studs to steel) |- |AS/NZS 1554.3||Structural steel welding - Welding of reinforcing steel |- |AS/NZS 1554.4||Structural steel welding - Welding of high strength quenched and tempered steels |- |AS/NZS 1554.5||Structural steel welding - Welding of steel structures subject to high levels of fatigue loading |- |AS/NZS 1554.6||Structural steel welding - Welding stainless steels for structural purposes |- |AS/NZS 1554.7||Structural steel welding - Welding of sheet steel structures |- |[[AS/NZS 1200|AS/NZS 3992]]||Pressure equipment - Welding and brazing qualification |- |AS/NZS 4855 || Welding consumables - Covered electrodes for manual metal arc welding |}
==Canadian Standards Association (CSA) Standards== The [[Canadian Staor the development, maintenance and publication of CSA standards.<ref>{{cite web|title=About CSA|url=http://www.csa.ca/cm/ca/en/about-csa|publisher=Canadian Standards Association|accessdate=7 November 2011|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111029122501/http://www.csa.ca/cm/ca/en/about-csa|archivedate=29 October 2011|df=}}</ref> The following is a partial list specific to welding:
