{{Infobox graduate school | name = Web@cademie | native_name = | image = Web@cadémie, formation labellisée Grande Ecole du Numérique.jpg | image_size = 150px | established = {{start date|2010}} | chancellor = [[Sophie Viger]] | motto = We are coders | type = private nonprofit tuition-free instutition | city = [[Le Kremlin-Bicêtre]], [[Lyon]], [[Nancy, France|Nancy]], [[Strasbourg]] | country = [[France]] | coor = {{coord|48|48|55|N|2|21|47|E|type:edu_region:FR|display=inline, title}} | level = | students = | parent = [[IONIS Education Group]], [[Epitech]], Zup de Co | website = {{url|webacademie.org}} }}
'''Web@cademie''' is a private, nonprofit and tuition-free [[computer programming]] school created and funded by French [[IONIS Education Group]] with several partners including [[Epitech]] and Zup de Co association. The school was first opened in Paris in 2010.<ref>{{fr}} [http://www.elle.fr/Societe/Le-travail/Reussir-au-boulot/La-web-cademy-l-ecole-d-informatique-qui-recrute-80-de-femmes-3387428# La Web@cadémie, l’école d’informatique qui recrute 80% de femmes]</ref>
Headquartered in [[Le Kremlin-Bicêtre]],<ref>{{fr icon}} [http://www.liberation.fr/societe/0101645556-l-ecole-qui-reconnecte-les-decrocheurs L'école qui reconnecte les décrocheurs]</ref> the school has branches in [[Lyon]]<ref>{{fr icon}} [http://www.digischool.fr/formation/la-webcademie-ouvrira-ses-portes-a-lyon-en-avril-2013-13694.php La Web@cademie ouvrira ses portes à Lyon en avril 2013]</ref>, [[Strasbourg]]<ref>{{fr}} [https://www.reussirmavie.net/Web-cademie-l-informatique-comme-seconde-chance_a1739.html Web@cadémie : l'informatique comme seconde chance]</ref> and [[Nancy, France|Nancy]].
Web@cademie delivers a two-year program dedicated to people with no degree and no background (without the [[French Baccalaureate]] but with a strong motivation in [[computer science]]<ref>{{fr icon}} [http://pro.01net.com/editorial/588287/la-web-academie-accueille-sa-troisieme-promotion-d-eleves-decrocheurs/ La Web Académie accueille sa troisième promotion d’élèves « décrocheurs »]</ref>). This is to help dropout students to have a job in a competitive industry.<ref>{{fr icon}} [http://www.lemouv.fr/diffusion-une-ecole-unique-en-france-la-web-academie Une école unique en France: la "web académie"]</ref>
The school has received the award ''[[:fr:Grande École du Numérique|Grande École du Numérique]]''.<ref>{{fr}} [http://www.leparisien.fr/le-kremlin-bicetre-94270/le-kremlin-bicetre-le-president-inaugure-l-ecole-du-numerique-30-09-2016-6165233.php Le Kremlin-Bicêtre : le Président inaugure l'école du numérique]</ref><ref>{{fr}} [http://www.echoidf.fr/2016/10/07/le-kremlin-bicetre-le-president-sur-les-bancs-de-la-webcademie/ Le Kremlin-Bicêtre – Le président sur les bancs de la Web@cadémie]</ref> The school is a non-profit organization and is entirely free.<ref>{{fr}} [http://www.reussirmavie.net/Web-cademie-l-informatique-comme-seconde-chance_a1739.html Web@cademie : l'informatique comme seconde chance]</ref> Major company such as [[Microsoft]] give financial support.<ref>{{fr}} [http://www.lesechos.fr/politique-societe/societe/0211233142219-derriere-les-portes-de-la-webcademie-2023130.php Derrière les portes de la Web@cadémie]</ref>
